President Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday approved the re-deployment of Mohammed H. Abdullahi as the substantive Minister of Environment. This was disclosed in a statement issued by the Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Boss Mustapha, which stated that the redeployment is to be effective as from today, April 6, 2022. “The President hopes that he would bring his wealth of experience to bear on his new assignment for the growth of the country,” the statement partly read. Recall that Abdullahi was the Minister of State for Science, Technology and Innovation.